+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017BEPve43AjXn89YmiEg6Kr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was built:\n\n**Files created:**\n- `src/scheduler.ts` — Core scheduling logic with all types and the `schedule` function\n- `src/index.ts` — Re-exports everything from `scheduler.ts`\n\n**Architecture:**\n\nThe scheduler uses a multi-strategy greedy approach with iterative improvement:\n\n1. **Cycle detection** (`detectCycles`): DFS-based cycle detection on the prerequisite graph, with explicit self-reference checking. Throws on any cycle.\n\n2. **Topological sort** (`topologicalSort`): Kahn's algorithm to produce an ordering that respects prerequisites.\n\n3. **Slot finding** (`findEarliestStart`): For a given event and room, finds the earliest valid start time considering capacity constraints, prerequisite completion times, gap requirements, and existing room occupancy.\n\n4. **Multi-ordering greedy passes**: Generates 5 different event orderings (by transitive dependents, shortest-first, longest-first, most-constrained-by-capacity, most-attendees) and runs a greedy scheduling pass with each. Picks the ordering that produces the most scheduled events.\n\n5. **Iterative improvement**: For any unscheduled events, attempts to fit them by swapping with scheduled events — removing one scheduled event, placing the unscheduled one, then re-placing the removed event elsewhere.\n\n**Key constraints honored:**\n- Room capacity (attendees <= capacity, default attendees = 1)\n- Time window (events within `[startTime, endTime]`)\n- Room gaps (configurable, default 15 minutes)\n- Prerequisite ordering with gap enforcement\n- Preferred room (hint, falls back to any valid room)\n- Cycle detection throws errors\n- Maximizes scheduled count, unplaceable events go to `unscheduled`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_